-speech spoken language modeling.\n\nTags: 压缩, LALM, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, LALM/音频标记-融合\n===3===\n# Step-Audio 2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2507.16632\nAuthors: Boyong Wu, Chao Yan, Chen Hu, Cheng Yi, Chengli Feng, Fei Tian, Feiyu Shen, Gang Yu, Haoyang Zhang, Jingbei Li, Mingrui Chen, Peng Liu, Wang You, Xiangyu Tony Zhang, Xingyuan Li, Xuerui Yang, Yayue Deng, Yechang Huang, Yuxin Li, Yuxin Zhang, Zhao You, Brian Li, Changyi Wan, Hanpeng Hu, Jiangjie Zhen, Siyu Chen, Song Yuan, Xuelin Zhang, Yimin Jiang, Yu Zhou, Yuxiang Yang, Bingxin Li, Buyun Ma, Changhe Song, Dongqing Pang, Guoqiang Hu, Haiyang Sun, Kang An, Na Wang, Shuli Gao, Wei Ji, Wen Li, Wen Sun, Xuan Wen, Yong Ren, Yuankai Ma, Yufan Lu, Bin Wang, Bo Li, Changxin Miao, Che Liu, Chen Xu, Dapeng Shi, Dingyuan Hu, Donghang Wu, Enle Liu, Guanzhe Huang, Gulin Yan, Han Zhang, Hao Nie, Haonan Jia, Hongyu Zhou, Jianjian Sun, Jiaoren Wu, Jie Wu, Jie Yang, Jin Yang, Junzhe Lin, Kaixiang Li, Lei Yang, Liying Shi, Li Zhou, Longlong Gu, Ming Li, Mingliang Li, Mingxiao Li, Nan Wu, Qi Han, Qinyuan Tan, Shaoliang Pang, Shengjie Fan, Siqi Liu, Tiancheng Cao, Wanying Lu, Wenqing He, Wuxun Xie, Xu Zhao, Xueqi Li, Yanbo Yu, Yang Yang, Yi Liu, Yifan Lu, Yilei Wang, Yuanhao Ding, Yuanwei Liang, Yuanwei Lu, Yuchu Luo, Yuhe Yin, Yumeng Zhan, Yuxiang Zhang, Zidong Yang, Zixin Zhang, Binxing Jiao, Daxin Jiang, Heung-Yeung Shum, Jiansheng Chen, Jing Li, Xiangyu Zhang, Yibo Zhu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Integrates discrete audio token generation into language modeling to achieve genuine end-to-end speech conversation and enhance responsiveness to paralinguistic information.\n  2. Leverages a latent audio encoder and reasoning-centric reinforcement learning to improve speech and audio understanding.\n  3. Incorporates retrieval-augmented generation and external tool calling, including a novel audio search tool for timbre and speaking style switching, to mitigate hallucination and leverage real-world knowledge.\n  4. Develops a multi-stage training strategy trained on millions of hours of diverse audio and textual data to ensure robust intelligence and expressiveness.\n  5. Introduces new evaluation benchmarks for paralinguistic understanding and tool calling to assess complex audio interaction capabilities.\n  6. Achieves state-of-the-art performance across multiple audio understanding and speech conversation benchmarks, outperforming existing open-source and commercial solutions.\n\nTags: LALM/音频标记-融合, LALM/对话型-交错标记, LALM/后训练-GRPO, LALM/训练-指令微调\n===4===\n# Emilia: A Large-Scale, Extensive, Multilingual, and Diverse Dataset for Speech Generation\narXiv: 2501.15907\nAuthors: Haorui He, Zengqiang Shang, Chaoren Wang, Xuyuan Li, Yicheng Gu, Hua Hua, Liwei Liu, Chen Yang, Jiaqi Li, Peiyang Shi, Yuancheng Wang, Kai Chen, Pengyuan Zhang, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of Emilia-Pipe, the first open-source preprocessing pipeline designed to efficiently transform in-the-wild multilingual speech data into high-quality training datasets for speech generation.\n  2. Construction of Emilia and Emilia-Large, comprising 101k and 216k hours of diverse, in-the-wild speech across six languages, making them among the largest open-source speech generation datasets.\n  3. Demonstration that models trained on in-the-wild Emilia data produce significantly more spontaneous and human-like speech while maintaining the intelligibility of models trained on traditional audio-book datasets.\n  4. Identification of a data scaling law in speech generation where performance improves with dataset size but exhibits diminishing returns beyond 100k hours.\n  5. Validation of the effectiveness of the Emilia-Large dataset for training robust multilingual and crosslingual speech generation models.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-多说话人\n===5===\n# SoulX-Transcriber: A Robust End-to-End Framework for Multi-Speaker Speech Transcription\narXiv: 2606.02400\nAuthors: Yuhang Dai, Haopeng Lin, Zhennan Lin, Jiale Qian, Jun Wu, Hanke Xie, Hao Meng, Hanlin Wen, Chuang Ding, Shunshun Yin, Ming Tao, Lei Xie, Xinsheng Wang\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n===6===\n# LLaMA-Omni: Seamless Speech Interaction with Large Language Models\narXiv: 2409.06666\nAuthors: Qingkai Fang, Shoutao Guo, Yan Zhou, Zhengrui Ma, Shaolei Zhang, Yang Feng\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposes LLaMA-Omni, a novel end-to-end model architecture that integrates a speech encoder, speech adaptor, LLM, and streaming speech decoder for low-latency, high-quality speech interaction with large language models.\n  2. Enables the simultaneous generation of text and speech responses directly from speech instructions without intermediate transcription, achieving a response latency as low as 236ms.\n  3. Introduces a streaming speech decoder based on a non-autoregressive Transformer and CTC that adaptively learns alignment between text and speech responses for real-time inference.\n  4. Constructs InstructS2S-200K, a speech instruction dataset tailored for speech interaction scenarios by rewriting text instructions and synthesizing corresponding speech responses.\n  5. Demonstrates that the model significantly outperforms previous speech-language models in both content and style while requiring highly efficient training of less than 3 days on 4 GPUs.\n\nTags: LALM, TTS, LALM/潜在表示, LALM/对话型-并行生成, LALM/对话型, TTS/功能-流式\n===7===\n# AISHELL6-whisper: A Chinese Mandarin Audio-visual Whisper Speech Dataset with Speech Recognition Baselines\narXiv: 2509.23833\nAuthors: Cancan Li, Fei Su, Juan Liu, Hui Bu, Yulong Wan, Hongbin Suo, Ming Li\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present AISHELL6-Whisper, the largest open-source Chinese Mandarin audio-visual whisper speech dataset featuring 30 hours each of parallel whisper and normal speech with synchronized frontal facial videos.\n  2. We propose an audio-visual speech recognition baseline based on the Whisper-Flamingo framework that integrates a parallel training strategy to align embeddings across speech types.\n  3. We introduce a lightweight projection layer specifically designed to adapt the model to whisper speech's spectral properties and bridge the acoustic gap with normal speech.\n  4. Our proposed model achieves a Character Error Rate of 4.13% for whisper speech and 1.11% for normal speech on the AISHELL6-Whisper test set.\n  5. Our approach establishes new state-of-the-art results on the public wTIMIT benchmark, demonstrating strong cross-lingual transferability.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/训练-SSL微调, ASR/训练-监督", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
